---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  title="The Arena: From Manual Notion to Automated Student Platform | Jams"
  description="How Jams built a gamified student analytics platform for The Arena, automating reports that used to take hours one at a time."
  projectName="The Arena"
  tags={['Web app', 'AI automation', 'EdTech', 'Gamification']}
  headline="From manual Notion to an automated student platform"
  intro="The Arena was capped by its tooling, not the market. We built the platform that let them scale the methodology they spent years developing."
  heroImage="/thearena-case-hero.png"
  heroImageAlt="The Arena student platform interface"
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-16">

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-neutral-900 mb-6">The Notion ceiling</h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-p text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">The Arena had built a real methodology for psychological coaching in high schools — cohort-based, data-driven, genuinely effective. The problem was the infrastructure running it. Every student got a duplicated Notion page. Every report was generated one at a time in ChatGPT, reviewed manually, then sent. Multiply that across cohorts, across schools, across the year. The business worked, but it could only grow as fast as the team could manage the manual work. It was not hitting a market ceiling — it was hitting a tooling ceiling.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-neutral-900 mb-6">The gamified ecosystem</h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-p text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">A two-sided platform: a management layer for The Arena team, and a student-facing app that made the coaching experience feel like a product worth using.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            {[
              { title: 'Ops center', body: 'Dashboard for managing schools, classes, and programs with a custom assessment engine.' },
              { title: 'Student app', body: 'Mobile-first interface where students create avatars and earn currency for completing self-development modules.' },
              { title: 'Report factory', body: 'Automated AI-powered psychological profile generation via OpenAI, with human review before delivery.' },
              { title: 'Progress tracking', body: 'Visual progress charts replacing static PDF reports.' },
            ].map(({ title, body }) => (
              <div class="card p-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
                <h3 class="font-display text-h4 text-neutral-900">{title}</h3>
                <p class="font-sans text-p-s text-neutral-700">{body}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-h2 text-neutral-900 mb-6">Tech stack</h2>
          <dl class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3">
            {[['Core', 'Bubble (logic and database)'], ['Reports', 'OpenAI'], ['Notifications', 'SendGrid'], ['Gamification', 'Custom avatar system and in-app currency']].map(([label, value]) => (
              <div>
                <dt class="font-sans text-p-xs text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">{label}</dt>
                <dd class="font-sans text-p-s text-neutral-900 font-medium">{value}</dd>
              </div>
            ))}
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section class="dark bg-neutral-950 rounded-2xl p-10">
          <p class="font-display text-h3 text-white">Shipped in 8 weeks. Now serves hundreds of students across multiple cohorts simultaneously. Reports that took hours individually are generated in batch.</p>
        </section>

        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-violet-500 pl-6 flex flex-col gap-3">
          <p class="font-display text-h4 text-neutral-900">"I was drowning in manual work. Jams transformed our unique methodology into a scalable product. Now the students love the app and we can generate hundreds of reports in the time it used to take to do one."</p>
          <footer class="font-sans text-p-s text-neutral-500">Julieta Lombroni, Founder at The Arena</footer>
        </blockquote>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</CaseStudyLayout>
